# === Reputation: milestone reward dialogue (long in-world lines; also used in NPC nodes) ===
aetherhaven.reputation.reward.continue=Continue
aetherhaven.reputation.reward.elder.50=The charter is not carved in stone forever. Here is the pattern for an amendments table. Craft it at your town planning desk once you know the schematic. Seat it in the hall and choose how the town's morning tithe leans.
aetherhaven.reputation.reward.elder.100=You have carried this place farther than anyone asked. Take this foundation stone: set a founder's monument where the charter allows. The treasury will remember.
aetherhaven.reputation.reward.innkeeper.50=You have kept this hall fed and honest long enough that I will trust you with the big table. Here is the banquet pattern—craft it at the town planning desk when you have the schematic, then set it in town. When the table is ready, you can call the Ledger Supper too: bread, cheese, pie, and a tithe that leans kind for a week. I will watch the hall while you serve it.
aetherhaven.reputation.reward.innkeeper.75=You have walked through enough long nights with us. When you lay out the Hearthglass Vigil, the town eats slower and kinder for a week. Fish, meat, vegetables, and a gentler fade for every need. That is how we keep each other standing.
aetherhaven.reputation.reward.innkeeper.100=You and this town share a name now. Berrycircle Concord is the light plate circle: salad, fruit skewers, popcorn, and a toast that lands. Serve it once and they will remember you warmer.
aetherhaven.reputation.reward.merchant.50=You have kept your word in bad weather and good. Here is the bench pattern. Craft it at your town planning desk once the schematic is yours. Appraisals are free on the bench; I still charge for mine.
aetherhaven.reputation.reward.merchant.100=You have put enough gold through this ledger to earn a jeweler's corner. The pattern is yours. Build it at the town planning desk. Set your gem, your metal, and the life you pour in, and the piece will come out true.
aetherhaven.reputation.reward.priestess.50=Gaia trusts you to walk the border between growth and ruin. Take this mix: crystal and life essence, shaped at the town planning desk. It reveals what should not stay, and lets you unmake a spawn with a single breath of powder.
aetherhaven.reputation.reward.farmer.25=You have earned my trust in the rows. I sketched an iron sprinkler. Craft it at the farming bench when you have water essence and iron.
aetherhaven.reputation.reward.farmer.50=Here is the thorium pattern: wider reach, same dawn rhythm. The Farming tab on the bench will show it once you know the schematic.
aetherhaven.reputation.reward.farmer.75=Cobalt holds pressure better. This page unlocks the third sprinkler tier, still one good soak at sunrise.
aetherhaven.reputation.reward.farmer.100=Adamantite and essence: the last sheet in the set. Place them with care. The town's fields will drink at dawn.
aetherhaven.reputation.reward.blacksmith.25=Stone for mortar, stone for patience. You have both, and it shows.
aetherhaven.reputation.reward.blacksmith.50=You've earned the forge's trust. Here is the schematic for a geode anvil. Craft it at your town planning desk when you have the bars and stone.

